The speaker claims that the game of love (`shughl-e-ishq-baazi`) is his sole occupation — indeed, his entire life. The opening verse states it plainly: **"My life is this: the game of love I play."** The poem's title already announces this: the speaker exists, and the playing of love is his one pursuit.
